init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the "Lost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The world is thrown into chaos as the elderly die off in droves.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are one of the lucky ones.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You have the world at your fingertips.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You are free to do whatever you want with the time you have left.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You rent a bus and take off.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You spend a week there, seeing all the sights and visiting all the famous movie sets.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You've always loved the snow and the cold.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You get there and it's just as beautiful as you remember.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You hike up the mountain and find a nice spot to sit and enjoy the view.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You feel so peaceful and happy.
